venue until you enter VMI  Continue on Letcher Avenue to VMI Parade Avenue  the first left Turn left on VMI Parade  passing in front of Smith Hall and the Marshall Library  Turn at the first left immediately beyond the Marshall Library  which will take you into the Center for Leadership and Ethics  parking lot  Traveling South on I 81  exit at 195  Take Exit 195 and turn right at the end of the exit ramp  US 11 South Proceed south on Route 11 to Lexington  about 5 miles  Follow the signs to downtown Lexington  US 11 Business Main Street Main Street will split and become Jefferson Street  one way South  Immediately turn right onto Letcher Avenue  Proceed on Letcher Avenue until you enter VMI  Continue on Letcher Avenue to VMI Parade Avenue  the first left  Turn left on VMI Parade  passing in front of Smith Hall and the Marshall Library Turn at the first left beyond the Marshall Library  which will take you into the Center for Leadership and Ethics  parking lot  For more travel information  please see the VMI visitor pages  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu Virginia Military Institute   Directions  skip to content VMI VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI Menu About About Us Administrative Offices Institute Report News  Photos  Videos VMI Archives Museums VMI Museum System The VMI Museum New Market Battlefield Stonewall Jackson House For Visitors Directions   Map Employment Parents   Fami